# Skill Standards

## File and Folder Naming

- Skill entry file MUST be named `SKILL.md` (case-sensitive, exact spelling)
- Folder name MUST be kebab-case, no spaces, no capitals
- Follow pattern: `{system}-{module}-{name}` (e.g., `bmad-rbtv-doc`)

## YAML Frontmatter

### Required Fields

- `name` — MUST match parent folder name exactly (e.g., folder `bmad-rbtv-doc` → `name: bmad-rbtv-doc`)
- `description` — MUST include what the skill does AND when to use it (trigger conditions)

### Optional Fields

Add only when relevant:

- `license` — License identifier (e.g., `MIT`)
- `compatibility` — Runtime version constraint (e.g., `claude-code >= 1.0`)
- `metadata` — Object with `author`, `version`
- `allowed-tools` — Array of permitted tool names

### Restrictions

- MUST NOT contain XML angle brackets (`< >`) in YAML frontmatter values
- MUST NOT include a `README.md` inside skill folders

## Size Limits

- RBTV thin loaders: under 35 lines
- General skills (non-RBTV): under 5,000 words

## Optional Subdirectories

Skills MAY include subdirectories for supplementary content:

- `scripts/` — Executable scripts
- `references/` — Reference documentation
- `assets/` — Static assets

RBTV thin loaders do not require these — they delegate to agents/workflows/tasks.

## Progressive Disclosure

Keep SKILL.md lean. Link to `references/` for heavy documentation rather than embedding it inline.
